    "analysis": "From the previous metric/trace/log summaries: multiple services show anomalies during the incident window, with strong duration and row_count spikes centered around ~16:25–16:35 UTC. trace.error_rate and log.error_count are zero, so this is a performance/throughput issue rather than increased failures. Among candidate services, trace.duration_p95 for ts-order-service shows a large relative spike (max ~1.76s vs p95 ~1.10s — ~60% breach) with earliest high around 2024-01-25T16:35:00Z; ts-travel and ts-route also show duration spikes but with smaller relative breaches. ts-auth-service has widespread resource KPI anomalies but with smaller relative deviations and earlier high times (~16:29). To decide root cause we need to compare resource-level breach severity for ts-order-service (the strongest duration anomaly) to see whether its own CPU/memory/socket/disk I/O metrics indicate resource saturation (which would make it the root cause), or whether its latency is likely caused by upstream/downstream dependencies. Next step: inspect ts-order-service metrics only, computing per-KPI breach ratios in the incident window (relative to global P95/P05) to identify the most severely affected resource KPI for ts-order-service.",
